race.comment: CORDINA (2) has been racing in stronger company than this, finishing 2.3L off the winner last start at Gosford most recently. Drops to country level now and the inside draw should see her get every chance in the run. Cole's claim comes in handy and she can get back to winning ways. FLYING CHEVROLET (10) won impressively first-up and showed it was no fluke last time out when beaten 0.2L out to 1425m at Moruya last time out. Third-up here, he gets Boudvillain in the saddle and with further improvement expected, he'll take beating. PEARLER (11) is racing well this time in work and can continue her good run of form. SPANISH NIGHT (5) has drawn soft and can improve fourth up.
